Network Comparison Table
1. PAN (Personal Area Network)
Definition
A PAN is the smallest type of network used for communication between devices within an individual's workspace.
Range
Typically 1–10 meters.
Technologies Used
Bluetooth
Infrared
USB
ZigBee
Examples
Smartphone connected to earbuds
Smartwatch connected to phone
Laptop connected to wireless mouse
Advantages
Easy setup
Low cost
Portable
Disadvantages
Limited range
Lower data speed
