Definition
A network that covers a small geographical area such as a room, office, building, or home.
Range
Up to several hundred meters.
Technologies
Ethernet
Wi-Fi
Fiber Optics
Components
Switch
Router
Access Point
Ethernet Cables
Examples
School computer lab
Office network
Home Wi-Fi
Advantages
High speed
Resource sharing
Better security
Disadvantages
Limited area
Maintenance cost
