12. Internet
Definition
The world's largest network of interconnected networks.
Features
Global connectivity
Information sharing
Cloud computing
Services
Web Browsing
Email
Video Streaming
Social Media
Online Banking
13. Client-Server Network
Definition
A centralized architecture where clients request services from a server.
Structure
Clients
   |
 Server
Examples
Gmail
Facebook
Banking Systems
Advantages
Centralized control
Better security
Disadvantages
Server failure affects clients
14. Peer-to-Peer (P2P) Network
Definition
A decentralized network where all devices can act as both client and server.
Examples
Torrent systems
Local file sharing
Advantages
Low cost
No central server
Disadvantages
Security concerns
Difficult management
